<A>__{stokers shovel coal. they are exhausted but they keep at it.}
<T>__{cut to:}
<A>__{patterson. waking in the car, rubbing his eyes. it's dawn. he stares out and from his face it's clear something special has happened. and now, at last }
<T>__{cut to:}
<A>__{something special and what it is, of course, is patterson's first view of the africa of his imagination. because the desert has ended, and now there are grasses and trees and one more thing bursts of animals. on both sides of the train. a flock of birds materializes here, a cluster of gazelles doing there amazing leap there. patterson is like a kid in a candy store.}
